tity: :runtime/req-b32f15717589ab56; What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to t-420f?; Session entity: :task/t-23f46700; Session entity: :runtime/req-610a00643d0da5c2; What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to ADR-FOUNDATION-017: THE HYPOTHETICO-DEDUCTIVE LOOP. The complete ...?; Session entity: :runtime/req-26db8b8d5fe5a27e; What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to ADR-FOUNDATION-017: THE HYPOTHETICO-DEDUCTIVE LOOP. The complete ...?; Session entity: :task/t-f12bff46; What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to t-420f?; Session entity: :config/concept-sigmoid-temperature; What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to :session/s-1774305837768?; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-count; Session entity: :runtime/req-7a15ccfacca53dc0; Session entity: :runtime/req-b8c002fa46194ed4; Session entity: :runtime/req-2d8a9c6b43d59c5f; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-sum; Session entity: :runtime/req-d54c975d94876db9; Session entity: :runtime/req-70b177f5d5e905eb; Session entity: :runtime/req-56076256f890d364; Session entity: :runtime/req-46141202d9a1af8b\nBUG FIX: Daemon routes observe/task/harvest with empty args causing parse errors. Fixed: only status and query are daemon-routable until arg marshaling implemented.; O(1) Approximate Spectral Gap; PROPOSAL: Wire approximate spectral into F(S) as structural_coherence boundary and into guidance as fragmentation detector. Closes Type 9 reflexive loop at zero cost.; Type 9 Reflexive Divergence Detection; Daemon Auto-Lifecycle; DAEMON-FIRST RESULT: CLI CPU 4.5s->0.02s (99.6% reduction). Wall time 3.0s = daemon computation (not CLI load). Observe through daemon: 0.16s. The daemon-first routing works — CLI skips store load entirely. Remaining wall time is daemon-side computation which can be optimized independently. INV-DAEMON-010 verified.; Session entity: unnamed entity; C9-PLAN-VERIFIED: Full implementation plan grounded in primary source review of concept.rs (5,362 LOC), seed.rs (5,314 LOC), signal.rs (1,465 LOC), methodology.rs (1,715 LOC), routing.rs (2,879 LOC). KEY FINDINGS FROM SOURCE: (1) concept_inventory() returns ConceptSummary with entity, name, member_count, embedding, variance, total_weight — NO agent provenance field exists. This is the gap C9-1 fills. (2) score_entity() at seed.rs:2109 uses formula 0.5*relevance + 0.3*significance + 0.2*recency — NO corroboration term. New formula: 0.4*relevance + 0.25*significance + 0.15*recency + 0.2*corroboration. (3) Agent identity is embedded in datom.tx.agent (AgentId field on TxId struct) — NOT stored as a :tx/agent datom attribute. Access pattern: for any datom d, d.tx.agent gives the AgentId. AgentId is BLAKE3-truncated 16 bytes from agent name string. (4) :exploration/depends-on attribute EXISTS in schema at schema.rs:1888 as Ref type with Cardinality Many — but is COMPLETELY UNUSED in the codebase. C9-2 activates this dormant attribute. (5) load_trajectory(store) at bilateral.rs:2004 returns Vec<f64> of F(S) history ordered by cycle number — ALREADY EXISTS, C9-5 reuses it directly. (6) MethodologyGaps struct at methodology.rs:1165 has 5 fields (crystallization, unanchored, untested, stale_witnesses, concentration) — extensible with stagnation: Option<StagnationSignal>. (7) format_concept_status() at concept.rs generates braid status concept lines — insertion point for corroboration display. (8) ContextSection enum at seed.rs:180 has 5 variants (Orientation, Constraints, State, Warnings, Directive). Directive is NEVER compressed (INV-SEED-006). Convergent findings go in Orientation section. (9) store.vaet_referencing(entity, attribute) provides reverse reference lookup — use for finding all observations assigned to a concept. (10) detect_aleatory() in signal.rs groups assertions by agent and flags multi-agent disagreement — pattern reusable for C9-4 contradiction detection across observations.; Spectral certificate is decorative. 20 datom attrs written never read. Zero consumers in routing guidance F(S). Type 9 reflexive divergence.; CRITICAL FINDING: Daemon is 85% complete (1925 LOC) but CLI opens LiveStore BEFORE trying daemon route. main.rs line 110 opens store (~3s), then line 156 tries daemon. If daemon is running, the 3s load is wasted. Fix: move daemon routing before LiveStore::open. Expected: daemon-routed status goes from 6-10s to ~500ms (socket RTT + daemon computation, zero deserialization on CLI side). This is the single highest-impact change remaining for INV-PERF-001.; DAEMON LIFECYCLE DESIGN: Three requirements for automatic, leak-free daemon lifecycle. (1) AUTO-START: try_route_through_daemon at line 730 checks sock_path.exists() and returns None if absent. Should instead fork a daemon subprocess, wait for socket, then route. Use std::process::Command to spawn 'braid daemon start' as a detached child with setsid(). (2) IDLE TIMEOUT: serve_daemon accept loop (line 869) should track last_request_time. If now - last_request > idle_timeout (configurable, default 5 minutes), initiate graceful shutdown. Prevents hanging processes and memory leaks. (3) CRASH RECOVERY: CleanupGuard (line 809) already handles RAII cleanup of socket and lock files. acquire_lock detects stale locks via kill(pid,0). These are sufficient — no additional crash recovery needed. Combined: first braid command auto-starts daemon, daemon self-terminates after 5 min idle, crash leaves no stale state.; Daemon-First Routing Order" :op :assert}
